    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\n Commerce Basics\n Get Started with Salesforce Commerce\n Import and Export Commerce Data\n Access to Commerce Stores\n Products and Pricing\n Configure Checkout for a Commerce Store\n Store Search\n Search Engine Optimization (SEO) for Commerce\n Commerce Einstein\n Einstein and Data Usage in Commerce Cloud\n Data Cloud for Commerce\n Store Management\n Commerce Promotions\n Considerations for Commerce Promotions\n Configure a Promotion\n Create a Promotion\n Create a Promotion Using a Template\n Create Promotions with Einstein\n Target Customers with a Promotion Segment\n Add a Promotion Tier\n Create a Coupon\n Define a Promotion Discount\n Choose What Qualifies for a Promotion\n Set Conditional Rules for a Promotion\n Localize Promotion Data\n Customize Promotions in Experience Builder\n Promotions in Checkout for B2B (Aura) Stores\n Example Promotions\n Prioritizing Promotions\n Remove a Promotion\n Sell Globally\n Website Design for Commerce Stores\n Publication and Activation\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nB2B COMMERCE AND D2C COMMERCE\nCreate a Promotion Using a Template\n\nUse a template to draft a promotion with products and categories from your store.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\nAvailable in: B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nIMPORTANT As of Summer ’24, there’s a refreshed Commerce app, which we encourage you to use. The navigation steps in this Help documentation reflect the new app. If you’re still using the previous app, now called the Commerce Storefront Console, see B2B and D2C Commerce Using the Commerce Storefront Console. For instructions on switching to the refreshed app, see Enable the Refreshed Commerce App.\nIn the navigation sidebar, select a store from the Store dropdown.\nClick Promotions, and then select Draft from Template.\nTo filter the list of templates based on the products and categories available in your store, in the Select a Template panel, select the store.\nSelect the template that you want to use, and click + to add the template details to your promotion.\nTo edit the promotion, update the fields in the Edit Your Promotion panel. In the Details section, update the applicable fields.\nSelect the store where you want to offer the promotion.\nSelect the audience.\nAfter selecting Specific Buyer Groups, search for the buyer groups that you want to add. These buyer groups are the same ones that are assigned to the store that you selected. If you don’t select buyer groups, the promotion applies to all the customers in the store.\nFor Name, enter the internal name for your promotion.\nTo activate the promotion as soon as you save it, select Active.\nTo improve performance, activate and prioritize only the promotions that you’re using. You can assign up to 50 manual and 50 automatic promotions to a store and its buyer groups.\nEnter a description for the promotion.\n(Optional) Select whether to exclude qualifying items from a discount. For example, if this is a buy 1 get 1 promotion.\nIn the Display Options section, update the applicable fields.\nFor Display Name, enter a name that customers see in the cart when the promotion is in effect.\nIf you don’t enter a display name, customers don’t know what discount they’re receiving.\n(Optional) Enter the terms and conditions.\nTo localize the display name and terms and conditions, use the Translation Workbench. See Translation Workbench.\nAdd discounts. See Define a Promotion Discount.\n(Optional) Select qualifiers. See Choose What Qualifies for a Promotion.\n(Optional) In the Advanced Option section, update the applicable fields.\nEnter a priority number.\nThe priority number determines which promotions apply first. The lower the number, the higher the priority. If you don’t enter a priority number, or if two applied promotions have the same priority, prioritization tiebreaker rules apply. See Prioritizing Promotions.\nSelect an exclusivity. See Prioritizing Promotions.\nLimit the number of times a customer can use the promotion in one cart.\nSelect a discount order.\nTo ensure that discounted items are cheaper than qualifying items, select a discount restriction.\nEnter the promotion’s start and end dates.\nClick Save.\nVerify that the promotion details are correct on each tab (segments, discounts, qualifiers, and so on).\nIf you haven’t already activated the promotion, when you’re ready, click Active.\nThe promotion isn’t available on your store until you activate it.\nSEE ALSO\nCreate Promotions with Einstein\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
